  "prompt": "Is there any good placement at northern India engineering college?",
  "response": "Northern India Engineering College, which was formerly known as Dr. Akhilesh Das Gupta Institute of Technology and Management (ADGITM) in Delhi, historically offered various engineering and management programs. When considering the quality of placements at any college, several factors are usually evaluated:\n\n1. **Placement Statistics**: Look at the percentage of students placed, the average package offered, and the highest package offered in recent years.\n\n2. **Recruiters**: Check the list of companies that visit the campus for recruitment. A diverse set of reputed companies across different sectors is often a good sign.\n\n3. **Alumni Network**: An active and successful alumni network can significantly impact placements positively.\n\n4. **Internship Opportunities**: Colleges that provide strong internship opportunities often see better placements, as internships can lead to pre-placement offers.\n\n5. **Training and Development**: Many colleges offer training programs to enhance students' soft skills, technical skills, and interview readiness, which can improve placement results.\n\nIt's important to conduct up-to-date research, such as visiting the college's official website, connecting with current students or alumni, and reading recent reviews, to get an accurate picture of the current placement scenario.",
